      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your tomato plants may be experiencing a case of \"leaf yellowing,\" which can be caused by a few different factors. One possibility is that your plants are not getting enough sunlight; tomatoes need about 6-8 hours of direct sunlight per day. Make sure they're getting plenty of light. Another possibility is that they're suffering from overwatering or poor soil drainage. Check the soil moisture and drainage, and adjust your watering schedule accordingly. If the problem persists, you may want to check for signs of pests or disease. If you find any, take steps to address those issues. Good luck, and don't forget to keep an eye out for any signs of new growth, as that will indicate that your plants are recovering.",
